{"lemma":"خَشَباتُ","slug":"خَشَباتُ","root":"خ.ش.ب","root_slug":"خ-ش-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ش-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خَشَب","root":"خشب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n10650","n10655","n10656"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wood, lumber, timber"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lignify, to become woody, to become woodlike"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to line with wood, to panel, to wainscot"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Denominal verb derived from خَشَب (ḵašab, “wood”)."},"ipa":["/xa.ʃab/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n10650","headword_ar":"خَشَبَ","root":"x$b","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$obN","text_ar":"خَشْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He mixed"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing (S, K) with ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":") another thing. (S.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He picked out, chose out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"selected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing: the verb thus having two contr. significations. (K, TA.)       -A2-  Also, (S, K,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He polished"},{"kind":"text","text":"a sword, (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by laying on it a broad and smooth spearhead and rubbing it therewith:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so accord. to ElAhmar, who relates that an Arab of the desert said to him, I said to a sword-polisher, “ Hast thou finished my sword? ” and he answered,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEamo","text_ar":"نَعَمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_il~aA A^an~iY lamo A^axo$ibohu","text_ar":"اـِلَّا اَنِّى لَمْ اَخْشِبْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Yes, except that I have not polished it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And [or, as in the TA, “ or ”]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sharpened"},{"kind":"text","text":"it. (K, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He forged"},{"kind":"text","text":"a sword: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fashioned"},{"kind":"text","text":"it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the file, without polishing"},{"kind":"text","text":"it: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made"},{"kind":"text","text":"it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imperfectly, not thoroughly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not well:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) thus, again, the verb has two contr. significations: (K:) also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he thus made"},{"kind":"text","text":"an arrow: (A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he shaped out"},{"kind":"text","text":"a bow, (AHn, K,) and an arrow, (TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a rough manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the first operation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without perfecting it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making it smooth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"even."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say of a sword, before it has been filed,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^aHosana maA xu$iba","text_ar":"مَا اَحْسَنَ مَا خُشِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How well has it been forged!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and in like manner one says of an arrow, when it has been filed, before the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safan","text_ar":"سَفَن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[with which it is smoothed] has been applied to it. (Skr, on a verse of Sakhr, cited below, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$iybapN","text_ar":"خَشِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$aba Al$~iEora","text_ar":"خَشَبَ الشِّعْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISk, S, A, K,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (A,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He said, spoke,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uttered, the poetry"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, A, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as it came,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unpolished, and unstudied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without affecting nicety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refinement, therein,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, A, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without study,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"labour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) Jereer did thus, and Farezdak trimmed his verses; but the verses of Jereer thus produced are better than the trimmed verses of Farezdak: (A, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Axt$bhu","text_ar":"اختشبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (A, K.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo yaxo$ibuwna AlkalaAma waAlEamala","text_ar":"هُمْ يَخْشِبُونَ الكَلَامَ وَالعَمَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They say, speak,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"utter, words, and do work, without affecting nicety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refinement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without study,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"labour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imperfectly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not thoroughly; inelegantly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not well."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~axa*a Als~ayofa xa$abFA","text_ar":"اِتَّخَذَ السَّيْفَ خَشَبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 8."}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","A","AHn","ISk"]},{"entry_id":"n10655","headword_ar":"خَشَبٌ","root":"x$b","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wood, such as is used in carpentry and the like; timber;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thick wood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) [a coll. gen. n.:] n. un."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$abapN","text_ar":"خَشَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of wood"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"timber"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) the pl. of the latter, (S, Msb, *) or of the former, (K,) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$abN","text_ar":"خَشَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, [i. e., accord. to the K, the pl. is the same as the sing., but properly speaking, as said above, this is a coll. gen. n.,]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu$ubN","text_ar":"خُشُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu$obN","text_ar":"خُشْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu$obaAnN","text_ar":"خُشْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) [which last is agreeable with analogy as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$abN","text_ar":"خَشَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu$obaAnN","text_ar":"خُشْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu$obN","text_ar":"خُشْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu$obN","text_ar":"خُشْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$abapN","text_ar":"خَشَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (JK.) The hypocrites are described in a trad. as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu$ubN biAll~ayoli","text_ar":"خُشُبٌ بِاللَّيْلِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuxubN biAln~ahaAri","text_ar":"صُخُبٌ بِالنَّهَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"Like"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"timbers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pieces of wood, in the night;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clamorous in the day;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning that they pass the night in sleep, without prayer. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlN xa$abN","text_ar":"مَالٌ خَشَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cattle that are lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emaciated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hazolaY","text_ar":"هَزْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in consequence of their feeding upon dry herbage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [And it seems that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$abN","text_ar":"خَشَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: for I find in the TA, and in a copy of the A which I believe to have been used by the author of the TA, mentioned as tropical,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlN xa$abN waHaTibN jazolN","text_ar":"مَالٌ خَشَبٌ وَحَطِبٌ جَزْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", app. meaning that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlN xa$ibN","text_ar":"مَالٌ خَشِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaTibN","text_ar":"حَطِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazolN","text_ar":"جَزْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazolN","text_ar":"جَزْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", I think, is here evidently a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hazolaY","text_ar":"هَزْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaTibN","text_ar":"حَطِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is explained in the S and K as signifying “ very lean or meagre. ”]"}],"source_refs":["A","K","Msb","S"]},{"entry_id":"n10656","headword_ar":"خَشِبٌ","root":"x$b","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rough,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axo$abuxa$iybN","text_ar":"اَخْشَبُخَشِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) the former applied in this sense to a male ostrich: (S:) and both signify anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gross,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"big,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rough,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd, S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$iybN","text_ar":"خَشِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and the first, (K,) applied to a man and to a camel, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tall, and gross, rude,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse, with bones uncovered by flesh, and hard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardy, and strong;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$iybN","text_ar":"خَشِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$iybiY~N","text_ar":"خَشِيبِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or these three signify, or signify also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rigid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tough:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, ISd:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$ibN","text_ar":"خَشِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardy, strong, and vigorous, in body:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) and the same, (JK,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$iybN","text_ar":"خَشِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose bones are uncovered by flesh, and whose sinews are apparent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard, or hardy, and strong:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK:) and the last, a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gross, big,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"camel: (S, TA:) a camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gross, coarse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rude, in make, and ugly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and a horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"big, in the bones."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 207.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$abN","text_ar":"خَشَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axo$abu","text_ar":"اَخْشَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)  Life"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which one is not dainty, nice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scrupulous."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S","TA","Kr","ISd","A","JK"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}